just_use card.go

# label: ELEGANT
# role: encodes domain knowledge

Card is the atomic unit of LynRummy. Load-bearing choices:

- **Double-deck awareness.** OriginDeck (0 or 1) tracks which physical
  deck a card came from. Equals considers origin (strict identity);
  IsDup ignores it (same rank+suit, either deck). Both are needed —
  a run can have two Kings of Hearts (one per deck), but a peel has
  to know whether two cards are "the same card."
- **Typed Suit enum.** `type Suit int` with explicit constants
  (Club=0..Heart=3). Lets `encoding/json` handle serialization
  natively, which is why the JSON shape IS the domain shape (no
  intermediate DTO / wire type).
- **CardColor derives from Suit.** Club/Spade=Black, Diamond/Heart=Red.
  Centralized in SuitColor so the coloring rule has one home.

Mirrors elm-lynrummy Card.elm — keep them in sync when changing shape.
